    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ 400\u00b0F/ Gas 6</p> <p>Chop the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong>\u00a0(skins on) into small bite-sized chunks</p> <p>Deseed the <strong>yellow pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thick strips</p> <p>Peel and\u00a0cut the <strong>red onion</strong> into wedges\u00a0</p> <p>Slice the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into rounds</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-roast-veg-tray-bake-basil-oil/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped sweet potato</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong>,<strong>\u00a0courgette</strong> and <strong>red onion</strong> to a tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of\u00a0<strong>olive\u00a0oil</strong></p> <p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up\u00a0</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-roast-veg-tray-bake-basil-oil/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 20 min or until the vegetables\u00a0are\u00a0starting to soften</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-roast-veg-tray-bake-basil-oil/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>Cypriot halloumi</strong> into 6<span class=\"text-danger\"> [12]</span> slices</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-roast-veg-tray-bake-basil-oil/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile,\u00a0chop the <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p> <p>Roughly chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p> <p>Grind the\u00a0<strong>chopped\u00a0basil</strong> and<strong> garlic</strong> with a pinch of<strong>\u00a0salt</strong> in a\u00a0<strong>pestle &amp; mortar</strong>\u00a0to form a paste</p> <p>Add 2-3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4-5 tbsp]</span>\u00a0<strong>olive oil</strong>\u00a0or enough to loosen and mix well \u2013 this is your\u00a0<strong>basil oil</strong></p> <p>Tip: if you don't have a pestle\u00a0&amp; mortar, chop the basil leaves very finely and mix with salt and olive oil</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-roast-veg-tray-bake-basil-oil/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After 20 min lay the<strong> halloumi slices</strong> over the<strong>\u00a0roast vegetables</strong> and return to the oven for 10 min or until the vegetables are cooked and\u00a0the halloumi is starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-roast-veg-tray-bake-basil-oil/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything is cooked, sprinkle over the<strong> pumpkin seeds</strong></p> <p>Return the tray to the oven for a further 4-5 min or until the\u00a0<strong>seeds</strong> are toasted<span class=\"text-highlight\"> \u2013 this is your <strong>Halloumi &amp; Roast Veg Tray Bake</strong></span></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-roast-veg-tray-bake-basil-oil/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the\u00a0<span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Halloumi &amp; Roast Veg Tray Bake</strong></span>\u00a0drizzled with the <strong>basil oil\u00a0</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
